Full Description: Synergy Recruitment is a headhunting firm that specializes in executive and technical recruitment based in Los Angeles with clients nationwide and internationally. The company specializes in headhunting and recruiting candidates with specific backgrounds, specific skills and often times – from specific companies. Synergy Recruitment was founded in 2005 by a small team of search professionals as a branch of SynCorp, a global consulting firm and partnership. The team began working with external clients and internally through exclusive Recruitment Process Outsourcing (RPO) contracts. In 2007 Synergy became recognized as a prime contractor to the United States, providing recruitment services to various government agencies as a sole source vendor.  The company eventually was consolidated in 2012 by the management consulting firm (Bristol & Bates LLC) to support internal hiring of the firms investments and also became an operating subsidiary and autonomous entity. The company is known for it's aggressive recruitment tactics and direct recruitment approach. The company often works with investors and exectuives of client companies who require unorthodox recruitment strategies such as infiltration or guerilla recruitment to further specific business growth objectives. Despite being a small organization the firm has made a significant impact on several organizations including several high-level build outs of entire sales organizations.  Client engagements have also ranged from growing venture funded start-ups to Fortune 500 organizations.

Description: Sweatdrops offers a mobilese ur interface to identify and measure the actions and behavior associated with the user's fitness life story.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Stories have always inspired people to take action. We wanted to build a tool that will allow people tell stories about their healthy lifestyle choices, and so inspire others to get active and healthy. Sweatdrops has designed a way to identify, track, and measure all the actions and behaviors associated with your fitness life story (FLS), and a simple mobile user interface to help you tell it. We define your FLS as the end-to-end experience across all your healthy activities. Specifically, your FLS is made up of 5 components: your personal progress, your accomplishments, the progress of others, the support you offer others, and community recognition. Currently, there is no single tool to track or share your FLS. Despite the technology available, avid runners and cyclists still write emails and send texts to each other to share information, motivate each other, and brag. Our team (made of athletes) feels this gap and has decided to build a tool specifically for people interested in sharing their FLS with each other. In the process, we developed a system to reward positive behaviors and activities, to further inspire (and incentivize) people to continue their healthy activities. Sweatdrops recognizes that fitness lifestyle is split into activity verticals, but within activities, there are similar patterns in the way that we interact with our communities and in the information that we share. Your FLS is full of rich data, allowing us to recommend activities and products, according to patterns in your behavior.  Our two big disruptions are: 1) that the FLS framework can be applied across activity verticals (ex: running, cycling, yoga) to address the fundamental needs of people who are passionate about fitness and 2) that the sharing currently taking place on email lists, text, Facebook can now take place on one convenient mobile app. To enable the measurement of your FLS, we’ve created a measurement system for tracking, sharing, and rewarding all actions across your fitness story—a common currency represented by sweat drops. Whether you go for a swim, upload a picture of a cross-fit class, or check in to a local juice bar with a friend, your actions will be earning sweat drops. They will act as a numeric representation of your FLS and will be redeemable for discounts on products and services. Committed and aspiring fitness enthusiasts love public recognition, but we believe they love rewards even more. There are multiple incentives to engage with the app.

Description: Saving Princess and other pets like her! 75% of the population are pet owners, as am I.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Saving Princess and other pets like her! 75% of the population are pet owners, as am I. I recently lost my pet in a vehicle accident. This death prompted the creation of 911 Pets. I was relocating back to Texas from Georgia, and I my car had not arrived. My 3 month old alligator pit, Princess, was struck by a car. I had no car to get her to emergency care, I could not use public transit and 911 is only for humans. Sadly Princess died about 15 minutes later. 911 PETS is a 24 hour emergency and routine care transportation and services company. It works similar to our 911 system. Pet parents call our Toll Free Number with their emergency. Live dispatchers will answer the calls and dispatch a Pet EMT unit. Each unit is a fully equipped mobile veterinarian medical unit, with a Veterinarian Assistant to assess problems and accompany the pet and parent to the nearest emergency care facility. We also offer Pet Pickup transportation services that provides transportation for pet and parent to and from vet appointments, along with low cost mobile veterinary clinics throughout the community or at your home. We need funding to get the operation up and fully operational. We need to purchase  •	(4) mobile van units fully equipped •	(1) mobile clinic van fully equipped ,  •	(3) Economy vehicles for the Pet Pickup Services.  •	We need to have the vehicles wrapped with 911 Pets Logo and toll free number. •	Funding to do a major marketing campaign to get the exposure and the word out  •	Salaries o	(6) drivers, ( o	6) assistants and  o	(2) On call Vets. Our plan it to bring 911 PETS to every major city in the US. Starting in Texas (June 2014 launch date) and will expand as we generate funds. We plan to offer franchise opportunities once we are up and fully operational in 5 major metropolitan areas.

Description: ForkTrotter is a community marketplace for homemade authentic ethnic food delivery.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: ForkTrotter is a community marketplace for homemade authentic ethnic food delivery. At ForkTrotter, Foodies can order ethnic meals that are homemade by talented Chefs who have a culinary heritage from their native countries. ForkTrotter was founded in 2015 when Mariam moved to New York from Morocco, and was desperately craving her mom’s Seven-veggies Couscous. In Moroccan restaurants, Mariam was puzzled each time she saw Falafel (a Lebanese/Palestinian snack) on the menu and was never able to get the homemade quality of the meals. She soon realized how non- mainstream ethnic cuisines are not authentic and there was no service, yet, for foodies to enjoy an ethnic meal that replicates the taste of eating a meal in another country. ForkTrotter allows you to cruise through a large selection of ethnic food from around world similar to a Globetrotter with a Fork. It is your gateway for culinary travel and discovery through multi-ethnic meals from remote cities and ethnic groups. ForkTrotter lets you replicate your past travel experiences by savoring meals you had during a time away, or simply for a really good meal, healthy, made with love, in an authentic way.  Eating well everyday is possible, and shouldn’t be a luxury. We bring convenience to you by allowing you to order your meals, schedule them, and get them delivered to you when you want, either to your office, your home, or to the park!

The members of the PERAB were appointed by the President from among distinguished citizens outside the Government who are qualified on the basis of achievement, experience, and independence.  The overall membership of the PERAB reflects a diverse set of perspectives from across the country and various sectors of the economy.    The PERAB meets periodically and solicits information and ideas from all sectors to promote the growth of the economy, establish a stable and sound financial and banking system, and create jobs.  The PERAB provides analysis and information directly to the President on the design, implementation, and evaluation of policies.  With respect to matters deemed appropriate by the President, the PERAB may provide information and recommendations to the National Economic Council  or any other agency with responsibilities related to the economy or financial markets.

Description: Anytime DD, LLC is a new company, which will be providing designated driver services to Marion County.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Executive Summary  Anytime DD, LLC is a new company, which will be providing designated driver services to Marion County, Indiana business patrons who drive their own vehicles when they partake in alcoholic beverages. Anytime DD will be operating as a franchise owner of StearClear. Anytime DD  is a term used to reflect the designated driver services provided throughout Marion County, Indiana. The presence of a designated driving service will allow patrons to mitigate their risks when they drive to the establishments at which they drink. Many drinkers of alcohol are electing to drive themselves to bars and other places of business for any number of reasons. Being able to do so with a reliable designated driver will benefit the client as well as contribute to making Marion County a safer place. Our Mission  Anytime DD aims to promote responsible drinking habits, help lower the burden placed on the state and local law enforcement agencies and provide safer roads in Marion County by lowering the amount of drunk drivers on the road through providing consistently reliable designated driver services, on-call all day every day.
